         .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 4. Serves as liaison and support to community chaplains and spiritual counselors.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 5. Maintains records of spiritual care services utilization and related activities for quality assurance, program development, and policies and procedures review and revision.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 6. Documents direct services and ongoing communication with community chaplains and spiritual counselors      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 7. Attends patient care conference and interdisciplinary group meetings as a member of the interdisciplinary group.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 8. Provides consultation, education, and support to the interdisciplinary group on spiritual care      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 9. Recruits community chaplains, spiritual counselors, and spiritual care volunteers adequate to meet patient and family / caregiver needs by developing community contacts and offering education through congregations about hospice care.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 10. Provides for funeral or memorial services for patients as requested.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 11. Plans periodic memorial services to meet the needs of personnel, volunteers, and community clergy / spiritual counselors working with the hospice team.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 12. Assists in supervision of spiritual care volunteers when assigned to patients / families / caregivers.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 13. Accepts and performs other related duties and responsibilities as required.    .form-row.col-md-12        .form-group.col-md-12          h4.text-dark POSITION QUALIFICATIONS        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 1. Graduate of accredited seminary or school of theology (BD, MDiv or equipment theological degree). Experience working with death and dying, individuals / family caregiver.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 2. Ability to work as member of interdisciplinary group.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 3. Comport in an interfaith setting        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 4. Ability to accept different lifestyles, cultures, beliefs and values        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 5. Ability to network with community clergy and congregations        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 6. Knowledge of and commitment to hospice philosophy of care.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 7. Hospice / experience preferred.    br    .form-row.col-md-12        .form-group.col-md-6            label.text-dark Full Name Of Applicant            input.form-control.waves-float.text-capitalize.text-dark(type='text' )        .form-group.col-md-6            .card                .card-body.bg-white                    div.flex.text-center                        div#sigbox                            input#signature(name='pg5signature' type='text' placeholder=' Sign here')                    br                    h4.mt-0.header-title.te